  "content": "<h3>ORDER PLACEMENT</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p><span style='color: #000000;'>You can place an order from four different places by tapping on the Buy/Sell option on the â€“ WatchList, Order Book, Portfolio and Scrip Overview.  </span></p>\r\n<p><iframe src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/FhFQtBw01L0' width='540' height='340' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen='allowfullscreen'></iframe> \r\n</p>\r\n<ol style='list-style-type: lower-roman;'>\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n\r\n<p><span style='color: #000000;'>On clicking the Buy/Sell Button, you will be directed to the Order Page. If you wish to change the segment, you can simply toggle between different segment cards. </span></p>\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n\r\n<p><span style='color: #000000;'>Choose from the different order types i.e. </span><strong><a title=' When you want your order to be executed at the current market price. '>Market</a></strong><span style='color: #000000;'><strong>, </strong></span><a title='When you want to place an order at a specified price (other than the market price). So, when the stock reaches the specified price, your order will be placed. If it does not, your order will be cancelled. '><strong>Limit</strong></a><span style='color: #000000;'><strong>, </strong></span><a title=''><strong>Stop Loss</strong></a><span style='color: #000000;'> and </span><a><strong>Stop Loss Market.</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n\r\n<p><span style='color: #000000;'>Select your product type by toggling between </span><a title='When you want to buy or sell shares on the same trading day. '><strong>Intraday</strong></a><span style='color: #000000;'> and</span> <a title=' When you want to buy or hold your positions for more days. '><strong>Delivery.</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n\r\n<p><span style='color: #000000;'>On entering the quantity, your amount will be auto-updated. (If you&rsquo;ve opted for Stop Loss or Stop Loss Market, then you will have to mention the </span><a title='The price at which your order should get triggered or activated.'><strong>Trigger Price</strong></a><span style='color: #000000;'><strong>. </strong></span><span style='color: #000000;'>If you&rsquo;ve opted for Limit and Stop Loss, you will have to mention the </span><a title='The specific price at which you want to buy/sell (not the same as market price).'><strong>Price</strong></a><span style='color: #000000;'>).</span></p>\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n\r\n<p><span style='color: #000000;'>Select the order validity &ndash; </span><a title='Validity to execute your order anytime during the market hours.  '><strong>Day</strong></a><span style='color: #000000;'> or</span> <a title='Immediate or Cancelled (Buying or selling your shares immediately; if not executed immediately, it will be cancelled.'><strong>IOC</strong></a><span style='color: #000000;'> (Immediate or Cancel).</span></p>\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>\r\n\r\n<p><span style='color: #000000;'>Then select the Buy/Sell button. </span></p>\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n</ol>",
